# =============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES TEMPLATE (frontend)
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env for local development.
# NEVER commit .env to git (it's in .gitignore).
#
# Only VITE_* vars are read by the frontend, and Vite embeds them statically at
# build time. In CI they are injected from SSM, not from this file (see
# .github/workflows/deploy.yml). Fill these in locally only to exercise the
# contact form's CAPTCHA against a real WAF integration.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS WAF CAPTCHA (Frontend)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Published by the infra repo to SSM:
#   VITE_WAF_INTEGRATION_URL <- /portfolio/<env>/waf-integration-url  (String)
#   VITE_WAF_API_KEY         <- /portfolio/<env>/waf-api-key          (SecureString)
# Both are CLIENT-side values, safe to embed in the frontend bundle: the integration
# URL loads the CAPTCHA JS SDK (defines window.AwsWafCaptcha); the API key is passed to
# AwsWafCaptcha.renderCaptcha() and is scoped by WAF to this env's token domains.
# Note the host is *.edge.captcha-sdk.awswaf.com.
VITE_WAF_INTEGRATION_URL=https://<integration-id>.edge.captcha-sdk.awswaf.com/<integration-id>/jsapi.js
VITE_WAF_API_KEY=<waf-captcha-api-key>

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Development Notes
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in your actual values in .env (which is gitignored).
# 3. The recipient address is NOT set here — it lives in AWS Secrets Manager and is
#    read by the Lambda at runtime (see terraform/secrets.tf).
# 4. Without these vars, the contact form's CAPTCHA can't render, so submit stays
#    disabled (in production) — this is expected for a local build with no WAF wired.
